---
target: git
version: 1
validations:
  - name: git-package-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/git/git.go
    contains:
      - "package git"

  - name: git-interface-defined
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "type GitManager interface" src/git/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: git-status-type
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "type GitStatus struct" src/git/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: commit-prefix-constants
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "intent:\|generated:" src/git/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: git-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: go test ./src/git/...
    exit_code: 0

  - name: git-tests-isolation
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that git tests:
      1. Create temporary directories for test repos (os.MkdirTemp or t.TempDir)
      2. Run git init in those temp directories
      3. Never reference or modify the project's own .git directory
      4. Clean up temp directories after tests
      5. Test actual git operations (add, commit, status) not just mocks
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/git/*_test.go"]
---

# Git Validations

Git integration must be thoroughly tested with real temporary repositories. The most critical invariant is test isolation - tests must never touch the project's own git state.
